column6: and little rolls (idk what was inside but it had roe on top). The Wagyu beef was delicious
column7: though it was a bit chewy :( Was a bit disappointed in the Wagyu. The mackeral was my favorite out this round. Had many different flavors going around and I think it had seaweed somewhere? something was crunchy but awesome. The anago was probably my least favorite of the whole omakase. It tasted good
column8: but the texture was very mushy... The tamago was yummy! We were told it was prepared differently and not the typical layers.
